CREATE TABLE Users (
    UserID INT IDENTITY(1,1) PRIMARY KEY,
    UserName NVARCHAR(100),
    Email NVARCHAR(150),
    CreatedDate DATETIME DEFAULT GETDATE(),
    IsActive BIT DEFAULT 1
);
‚úÖ This creates a Users table with:

UserID: Auto-incremented primary key

UserName, Email: Text fields

CreatedDate: Defaults to current date

IsActive: Boolean (1 = active, 0 = inactive)

‚ûï 2. Insert Data
sql
Copy code
INSERT INTO Users (UserName, Email)
VALUES 
('John Doe', 'john.doe@example.com'),
('Jane Smith', 'jane.smith@example.com'),
('Alice Brown', 'alice.brown@example.com');
Adds three users to the Users table.

üîç 3. Select Data (Top 100 rows)
sql
Copy code
SELECT TOP 100 *
FROM Users
ORDER BY CreatedDate DESC;
Retrieves the latest 100 users from the table.

‚úèÔ∏è 4. Update Data
sql
Copy code
UPDATE Users
SET IsActive = 0
WHERE UserName = 'John Doe';
Marks John Doe as inactive.

‚ûï 5. Add a New Column (Optional)
sql
Copy code
ALTER TABLE Users
ADD Department NVARCHAR(50);
Adds a new column to store the user‚Äôs department.

üîé 6. Filter / Search
sql
Copy code
SELECT *
FROM Users
WHERE IsActive = 1
AND Email LIKE '%@example.com';
Shows active users whose email ends with @example.com.

üßÆ 7. Count Users
sql
Copy code
SELECT COUNT(*) AS TotalUsers
FROM Users
WHERE IsActive = 1;
Returns the number of active users.
